        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} relatives. His aunts, their partners, and the kids of his cousin. Oh, and dog Oscar, not to forget. After arrival, we enjoyed a relaxing afternoon with dog cuddles, cake on the terrace, followed by a few rounds of table tennis. The pool was tempting, and although I originally only wanted to dip my feet in, the two kids made it impossible to stay dry. I was quickly in the water - a welcome bit of fun that we all enjoyed with laughter. </p>
        <p> In the evening, the day was rounded off with a delicious barbecue meal and cool drinks. We slowly ended the day in nice conversations, but we knew that the next day would be exciting again. </p>
        <p> Today started calmly with a cozy breakfast, where we were spoiled with boiled eggs and other treats. Steffi continued to cuddle Oscar into the ground. We discussed that we would stay until Monday before heading to the Elbe Sandstone Mountains. Strengthened, we set off at lunchtime to meet with Kerstin, Thomas, and the two girls for a hike. </p>
        <p> It started with a little confusion when we ended up at the wrong parking lot. But Uncle Thomas, who came to meet us, drove us the 500 meters to the right meeting point. The hike then really started: first a small round around the lake and then off into the forest to the Muldenberg Dam. Steffi went ahead at some point without much motivation - her motto: "If I stop, I won't get any further!" </p>

