        <p> After about eight kilometers, we reached the Flößerstube in Muldenberg and treated ourselves to cake and drinks. We almost unanimously decided to take the train back. On the way to the train, the girls still had fun when they pulled themselves across a pool with a raft. </p>
        <p> Back in Schöneck, we said goodbye to aunt, uncle, and the girls, but took some time to explore the IFA holiday complex. There is really a lot to discover here - hiking trails, ski courses, wellness programs, and much more. After a small dinner at the hotel, we drove back to Aunt Babsi and Uwe, who were still out. We made ourselves comfortable in front of the TV, played a round, and talked until they came back. Then it was time to go to bed and digest the experiences of the day. </p>
        <p> So it was a day full of beautiful experiences. We would be happy to have many more! Until tomorrow </p>
